metadata.description:
Updated Jan 2017


Hurricane Hazel was one of the most destructive hurricanes to hit the N. Carolina coast.  This category 5 hurricane caused flooding and wind damage as far North as Canada.  This 2 ½ minute video shows the aftermath of Hazel on CarolinaBeach and WrightsvilleBeach.  The original 8mm footage was taken by David Nicholas Chadwick, Jr and restored by J. Clement.  The photographer and his family appear in a few shots.

 

While there are many pictures of the destruction, the effect of the wide beach pans are more effective than the usual black and white stills.  The 8mm silent film is presented in high definition 720P/30fps. The processing included stabilization, noise removal, spot removal, bad frame removal at transitions, and frame rate doubling.  Some spots and discoloration were removed by hand rotoscoping.  Severe damage was repaired by cloning from undamaged frames or areas and no details were added.  The software included Neat denoiser, Virtual Dub Deshaker, Virtual Dub Spot Remover, Movie Edit Pro, and Photoshop extended, SVP AviSynth.

metadata.title: Huzhu Mongghul Wedding
metadata.creator: Zhu Yongzong, Kunchok Gelek, Limusishiden, and Jugui
metadata.description:
Mongghul Rog Warigu Log

Nenga Mongghulni mazii, hurin ghuji yiri awujin rog warigu logni ne hara fanni muxi ne Fulaan Nara ghajarini Wayog Ayili (xni ziiwuni kudu) da Zhanka Ayilidi (xni aaguni kudu) ghoori shaixangjiila liuki bo rghasanna. Nera hgengiini ne Mongghulni diidangmani log shdaari yiughaja. Dogu niumalang ne 2010 fandi nera yiijinni hgengiiniini kuja qughuaxja. Nensa huina kun ne Mongghul diidangmadini amakiji mazii hurin ghuanakiji mudegiigisa nenga rog warigu logni hana nige rjesa jiu digiisan shdaari qimu mudegha shdaguna! Bu ne Mongghul, nengani haran fansa muxi mudewa liuki borigha shda sgilisa baisa hguaiyii yan yanma ne njina ne sanbara zui duralajin! 


 Huzhu Mongghul (Tu) Wedding

This Mongghul wedding was filmed by Zhu Yongzhong and Kunchok Gelek in Huzhu Mongghul (Tu) Autonomous County, Haidong Region, Qinghai Province, PR China on the 26th and 27th days of the first lunar month of 1999. This unique material shows the groom’s side sending two matchmakers and the bride-taker to the bride’s home on the afternoon of the 26th. The next day, the bride is taken to the groom’s home. Jugui (a relative of the groom) and Limusishiden coordinated with both families to make the filming a success. Traditional dancing, joking, singing, presentation of food and liquor, horse riding, and much more are all here. In 2010, the year this documentary was uploaded here, it was impossible to find such a traditional Mongghul wedding. The groom, Danjanduriji (b. ~1980), is from Wayog Village, Wushi Town and the bride, Limuhua (b. ~1979), is from Zhanka Village, Songduo Township. The film was edited by Jugui and Limusishiden in 2000 in Xining.
metadata.subject: Huzhu; Mongghul; Tu; Ping'an; Qinghai; wedding; marriage

metadata.title: Huzhu Mongghul (Tu, Monguor) Love Songs
metadata.creator: Limudanzhuu
metadata.description:
Ghadani dogni ne muxiha hana Mongghulla dolana. Huina Qidari kun ne Wuuzin ghajarishdi rjaha dii jona jona Qidarila dolaxja. Dan hansi Mongghulni yangla dolana. Yangni darang hgala shdaji gua. Dii huina huinaha ne furi ghajariâMiinhu, Liinxa ne ghajarini yangni Mongghul ghajarishdi rua rjaha dii hana yiila ne guura ghajarini kunhgini yangniini yangladaxja. Ne lukisan nera ghuran yirila darang Mongghulla dolaja. Huina nigiijiniini Qidarila dolaja jida yangni hansi Mongghulna. Niumalang hana yixi Qidarila dolangi ne yirihgi Mongghulla dolagii gina jida Qidarishdi alidadina. Ne shaixanglasanra muxigu hurin-jirighun finzhunsa muxi yiigualani Mongghulla dolaja, huinaguniini nijeeriniini Mongghulla dolaja hgengiiniini Qidarila dolaja. Ndiriigu Qinhai ugola dolaja, dan Mongghulni yangna. 
 
Limudanzhuu (b. 1966) of the Mongghul (Monguor, Tu), ethnicity, graduated from Inner Mongolia Forestry College, Huhehaote City, and was assigned to work in the Huzhu Forestry Bureau, Huzhu Mongghul (Tu) County. In his free time he often visits Mongghul villages to film Mongghul life. In this film, the first 26 minutes are love songs sung in Mongghul; the remaining songs are sung in Mongghul and local Qinghai dialect, but all are Mongghul melodies. A couple of love songs are very old ones. 

These songs were filmed on the 13th and 14th days of the tenth lunar month, 2004 in Ms. Changminjiiâs home in Qasizi Village, Donggou Township. The singers are Changminjii, Yayixji, and Niigari. 

The three singers reported that before 1984, Mongghul love songs were sung in Mongghul, but this has now is much less frequent. Now Mongghul love songs are sung in Chinese.â

The program was filmed by Limudanzhuu and made to a VCD on the third day of the 10th lunar month in 2007 at his home.
